abstract: >-
  BuildOcc provides LLM-based occupant agents for building energy simulation,
  grounded in American Time Use Survey (ATUS) microdata. It offers a Python
  agent library, a REST API, and an MCP server, with ATUS-grounded activity
  scheduling across four demographic strata, persona generation with EIA RECS
  appliance priors, a Park et al. (2023) memory stream, a demand-response signal
  typology, and two-tier behavioral and energy validation metrics.
